title: 'End of the holiday': Tourists watch in horror as Tenerife wildfires force thousands to evacuate
description: For just a small moment on Friday, the Canarian authorities thought they had Tenerife's worst wildfire in over four decades under control.

title: 'Abnormal situation' at Russian spacecraft
description: Russia has reported an "abnormal situation" at its moon-bound spacecraft which launched earlier this month.

title: Six-year-old girl among seven dead in Russian missile strike on Chernihiv
description: A six-year-old girl is among seven people who died after a Russian missile strike on the historic city of Chernihiv in northern Ukraine.

title: Killer whale Lolita dies after 52 years in captivity
description: Lolita, an orca held captive for more than half a century at the Miami Seaquarium, has died at the estimated age of 57 from suspected kidney disease.

title: Canadian city a 'ghost town' as state of emergency declared over spreading wildfires
description: Thousands have fled their homes as huge wildfires burned near the capital city of Canada's Northwest Territories.

title: West Ham midfielder withdrawn from Brazil squad amid betting investigation
description: West Ham midfielder Lucas Paqueta has been withdrawn from the Brazilian World Cup qualifiers squad amid concerns surrounding an FA and FIFA betting investigation.

title: FIFA boss insists organisation is 'a pioneer' for women's football after criticism over equal pay comments
description: FIFA President Gianni Infantino has told Sky News that men should not be "imposing what they think women football should be" and copying the men's game in a "bad way".

title: Neymar arrives in Saudi Arabia on almost empty jet after PSG departure
description: Neymar has arrived in Saudi Arabia after agreeing a deal to move from French side Paris Saint-Germain to the Saudi Pro League.
